<manpage
author="J&oe;rg Wittenberger"
date="27. 4. 1995"
>epstogif
<short>convert Encapsulatet PostScript to GIF
<synopsis>
<code>epstogif <var>eps-file gif-file
<config>
The compilation of the source depends on the following parameter
entities:

<desc

<dt<code>mkinc</dt>If this parameter entity is defined on
compilation of the source (e.g., <code/-i mkinc/ given to &sdc;) a
file to be included into a shell script is compiled from the source
instead of the executable script. This script converts from
<code/$EPSTOGIFFROM/ to <code/$EPSTOGIFTO/.

<dt<code>local</dt>A version which works on the local host is
generated.

<dt<code>remote</dt> A version working on a remote host is generated.

</desc>

The file instdir (anywhere in the <code/DOCPATH/) must contain the
absolute path name of the installation directory of &sdc;.

<descript>
Epstogif converts a encapsulated PostScript file into a GIF file.

It needs ghostscript, pstogif and the pbm tools for it's operation.

The remote version needs a proper set up of the <code/.rhosts/ file on
the remote accont and some files in the directory 
<code>~/remote</code> on the called host.

<![ %Literat [
The source:
<literate file="epstogif">
<![ %mkstand [ <verb>
#!/bin/sh
EPSTOGIFFROM=$1
EPSTOGIFTO=$2
</verb> ]]>

<![ %local [ <rverb>
GS_LIB=&instdir;/bin
export GS_LIB
&instdir;/bin/pstogif $EPSTOGIFFROM $EPSTOGIFTO >/dev/null 2>/dev/null
</rverb> ]]>

<![ %remote [ <verb>
EPSTOGIFRFROM=`basename $EPSTOGIFFROM`
rcp $EPSTOGIFFROM $REMOTENAME@$REMOTEHOST:remote/$EPSTOGIFRFROM
rsh $REMOTEHOST -l $REMOTENAME "cd remote;\
  ./pstogif $EPSTOGIFRFROM $EPSTOGIFTO" >/dev/null 2>/dev/null
rcp $REMOTENAME@$REMOTEHOST:remote/$EPSTOGIFTO $EPSTOGIFTO
rsh $REMOTEHOST -l $REMOTENAME rm -f remote/$EPSTOGIFRFROM remote/EPSTOGIFTO
</verb> ]]>

</literate> ]]>
<env>
The remote version depends on the environment variables

<desc
<dt/$REMOTEHOST/ The host which does the work.
<dt/$REMOTENAME/ The account name of the user on the remote host.
</desc>

The inclusion version uses variable names starting with
<code/EPSTOGIF/ for it's putposes.

<files>
<desc
<dt>$REMOTENAME@$REMOTEHOST:.rhosts</dt>must include the users
machine.
</desc>

